DIROFILARIASIS - RUSSIA (KIROV REGION)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 7 April 2008
Source: IA Rosbalt-Privolzhie [in Russian transl. corr,ATS and edited]
<http://www.rosbalt.ru/2008/04/05/471931.html>


Cases of tissue dirofilariasis have been recorded in the Kirov region
---------------------------------------------------------------------
This year 2 cases of human dirofilariasis have been recorded in the
Kirov region, the 1st human cases in the region according to the
press-service of Rospotrebnadzor (Federal Service for Consumer
Protection and Human Well-Being) in the Kirov region.

The 2 cases were found in the Kotelnichsky district of the Kirov
region. The 2 patients are believed to have been infected by mosquito
bites. The reservoir of infection is infected domestic dogs, cats and
rarely wild carnivorous(wolves, foxes etc.). Transmission to humans
and animals are seen from May to September.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The areas where dirofilarias is found is expanding due to
epidemiologic, ecologic and climatic factors, including a high level
of infections in dogs and widespread presence of the mosquito vector.
According to Rospotrebnadzor in the 2007 dirofilariasis was recorded
in the Tula, Voronezh, Belgorod, Ivanovo, Vologda, Camara, Nizhniy
Novgorod, Saratov, Chelyabinsk, Orenburg, Penza, Omsk, Ulyanovsk,
Kurgan, Amur (Blagoveschensk), Krasnodar, Krasnoyarsk and Altay
regions of Russia. See:
<http://www.rospotrebnadzor.ru/docs/letter/?id=1477> - Mod.NP]

[[Human infection with _Dirofilaria_ spp. is rare and causes
subcutaneous nodules. The nematode is transmitted by mosquitoes and
the reservoir is cats and dogs (dog lung worm). - Mod. EP]
